# Assignment description
## Part 2 - Required

Please answer the following questions with no more than 2-3 lines

1- What are Mutation Observers in JavaScript?

2- Explain 3 different CSS selectors.

3- What is the difference between `SessionStorage` and `LocalStorage` in HTML5?



THE ANSWER'S :


1-What is the difference between SessionStorage and LocalStorage in HTML5?

The localStorage :
Web page can be viewed simplicitily for greater storage capacity ,object stores the data with no expiration date,
The data will not be deleted when the browser is closed and will be available the next day, week, year
The data is send back to the server for every HTTP request, 


The session Storage :
object is equal to the localStorage object, changes & Data is only available inside window it was set, except that it stores the data for only one session.
 The data is deleted when the user closes the specific browser tab.



2- Explain 3 different CSS selectors ? 

.Element Type Selector: this selector must match one or more HTML elements of the same name
.ID Selector : This selector matches any HTML element that has an ID attribute with the same value
. class selector :matches all elements on the page that have their class attribute set to the same value as the class,


3-What are Mutation Observers in JavaScript? 

The MutationObserver interface provides the ability to watch for changes being made to the DOM tree.


